  "prompt": "Can I deposit cash without cheque in SBI?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deposit cash without a cheque in State Bank of India (SBI) through several methods:\n\n### 1. **Cash Deposit Machine (CDM):**\n   - Locate a Cash Deposit Machine at your nearest SBI branch.\n   - Insert your debit card and enter your PIN.\n   - Choose the \"Cash Deposit\" option.\n   - Enter the account number where you wish to deposit the cash (if it's not linked to your debit card).\n   - Insert the cash into the machine. The machine will count the notes and display the total amount.\n   - Confirm the transaction and collect the receipt.\n\n### 2. **Branch Counter:**\n   - Visit any SBI branch.\n   - Fill out a **Pay-in Slip** (available at the branch) with details like your account number, name, and the amount to be deposited.\n   - Submit the pay-in slip along with the cash to the teller at the counter.\n   - The teller will process the transaction and provide you with a receipt.\n\n### 3. **Cash Deposit through Business Correspondents:**\n   - In some rural or remote areas, SBI has Business Correspondents (BCs) who can accept cash deposits on behalf of the bank.\n   - Provide your account details and the cash to the BC, who will process the deposit and give you a receipt.\n\n### 4. **Mobile Banking App:**\n   - If you have the SBI YONO or SBI Anywhere Personal app, you can use the \"Cash Deposit\" feature to locate an ATM or CDM for depositing cash.\n   - Follow the instructions on the app to complete the deposit.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- Ensure you have your account number handy.\n- For deposits made at the counter, a valid ID proof may be required for larger amounts.\n- There may be limits on the amount of cash you can deposit in a single transaction or day, depending on the method used.\n\nAlways retain the receipt for your records until the transaction is reflected in your account statement.",
